ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Only take it if required. Homework is time consuming and lectures can be hard to follow.
Very difficult, you will feel lost a lot of the time, but you will learn a lot. You need a solid math foundation, and I would only recommend it after having a strong math class.
Very useful, ESP if Michael is teaching it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was another course that helped with my critical thinking abilities. The material covered will not directly contribute to my research.
Somewhat. Not always applicable to real life engineering, but it was a good class to have.
Understand the various approximations and assumptions that are usually unexplained. New skill set in math learned to handle flow probs.
